dc_title_s: Sketch survey of the north-east portion of New Britain by Mr. Wilfred Powell, 1878-9
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Volcanoes are labeled. Includes information on navigability of waterways. Sand banks, reefs, breakers, and shoals are shown. Includes inset map of New Britain, New Ireland, Solomon Islands, and eastern New Guinea [scale ca. 1:13,000,000 at 5° S]. Conjectural coastline shown by dotted lines. From: Proceedings of the Royal Geographical Society and monthly record of geography. Vol. 3 (1881), no. 2, pp. 84-97; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J6873
